WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:17.350 --> 00:00:19.269 position:50% align:center
[ASAI] Sakurai Shinichi
started working here

00:00:19.352 --> 00:00:21.146 position:50% align:center
part-time last year.

00:00:21.229 --> 00:00:23.898 position:50% align:center
He looks a little scary,
but he takes his work seriously

00:00:23.982 --> 00:00:27.402 position:50% align:center
and our regulars only have
good things to say about him.

00:00:27.485 --> 00:00:30.447 position:50% align:center
But most of all...

00:00:30.530 --> 00:00:33.616 position:50% align:center
...that boy is fine.

00:00:35.702 --> 00:00:37.579 position:50% align:center
[ASAI]
Gah! I can't stop staring!

00:00:37.662 --> 00:00:39.914 position:50% align:center
Look at him,
he's basically perfect!

00:00:39.998 --> 00:00:43.335 position:50% align:center
He looks thin, but he's got some
real muscles under there!

00:00:43.418 --> 00:00:46.087 position:50% align:center
S'cuse me, handsome!
We're ready to check out now.

00:00:46.171 --> 00:00:47.589 position:50% align:center
Uh...

00:00:47.672 --> 00:00:49.382 position:50% align:center
[ASAI]
I doubt he's even noticed this,

00:00:49.466 --> 00:00:52.135 position:50% align:center
but he has plenty of
fans around here.

00:00:52.218 --> 00:00:55.388 position:50% align:center
Gosh, you're so tall, Sakurai!
How tall are you?

00:00:55.472 --> 00:00:56.765 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
About five eleven.

00:00:56.848 --> 00:00:58.391 position:50% align:center
Wow, that's impressive!

00:00:58.475 --> 00:01:00.143 position:50% align:center
Have you ever played any sports?

00:01:00.226 --> 00:01:01.936 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] Just the
swim team in high school.

00:01:02.020 --> 00:01:04.064 position:50% align:center
[HOUSEWIFES]
Oh my, how interesting!

00:01:04.147 --> 00:01:07.567 position:50% align:center
[ASAI] I love it! Yes!
Great questions, ladies!

00:01:07.650 --> 00:01:12.989 position:50% align:center
And swimmers are so hot.
I mean, you can see everything!

00:01:14.824 --> 00:01:17.952 position:50% align:center
[ASAI] Look at me, picking up
juicy tidbits here at work!

00:01:18.036 --> 00:01:20.747 position:50% align:center
I'm making so much progress!

00:01:21.956 --> 00:01:23.166 position:50% align:center
[CAFÉ OWNER]
Your heart doesn't really seem

00:01:23.249 --> 00:01:24.834 position:50% align:center
to be in it today, Ami.

00:01:24.918 --> 00:01:26.252 position:50% align:center
[ASAI]
Huh?

00:01:26.336 --> 00:01:28.296 position:50% align:center
Getting lost in
thought is normal.

00:01:28.380 --> 00:01:31.174 position:50% align:center
But try to remember,
you are on the clock.

00:01:31.257 --> 00:01:34.177 position:50% align:center
You gotta be careful
when doing busy-work.

00:01:34.260 --> 00:01:37.305 position:50% align:center
You could easily lose track
of what you're doing.

00:01:38.223 --> 00:01:40.266 position:50% align:center
Right. I'm sorry.

00:01:40.350 --> 00:01:42.310 position:50% align:center
I understand
your interest, though.

00:01:42.394 --> 00:01:45.313 position:50% align:center
Now go ahead and clear
that empty table, okay?

00:01:45.397 --> 00:01:47.440 position:50% align:center
Thanks, Dad, I will.

00:01:47.524 --> 00:01:49.693 position:50% align:center
[ASAI] Dad has this way of
coming across all gentle 

00:01:49.776 --> 00:01:52.570 position:50% align:center
and sweet even when he's
being strict as heck.

00:01:52.654 --> 00:01:55.073 position:50% align:center
But how can I concentrate
when fate brought Sakurai

00:01:55.156 --> 00:01:55.949 position:50% align:center
and me together today?

00:01:56.032 --> 00:01:57.575 position:50% align:center
[door clatters]

00:01:57.659 --> 00:01:59.911 position:50% align:center
Sakurai! Hey!

00:03:32.253 --> 00:03:34.172 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
So. Back again, huh?

00:03:34.255 --> 00:03:36.091 position:50% align:center
Don't you have
anything better to do?

00:03:36.174 --> 00:03:37.842 position:50% align:center
Well, I could ask you
the same thing, 

00:03:37.926 --> 00:03:40.470 position:50% align:center
working this hard on
a Sunday and all!

00:03:40.553 --> 00:03:42.681 position:50% align:center
[ASAI]
Wait, what? Who's this?

00:03:42.764 --> 00:03:43.765 position:50% align:center
Hello there, Hana.

00:03:43.848 --> 00:03:44.599 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI giggles]

00:03:44.683 --> 00:03:46.101 position:50% align:center
[ASAI]
Dad knows her, too?

00:03:46.184 --> 00:03:47.310 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI] 
Up top! Yeah!

00:03:47.394 --> 00:03:48.728 position:50% align:center
All right!

00:03:48.812 --> 00:03:51.981 position:50% align:center
[ASAI]
Ugh. Remember your dignity!

00:03:52.065 --> 00:03:54.359 position:50% align:center
[CAFÉ OWNER] Peak time's just
ended, so it's pretty slow.

00:03:54.442 --> 00:03:55.860 position:50% align:center
Sit wherever you like.

00:03:55.944 --> 00:03:57.237 position:50% align:center
--[UZAKI] Thanks!
--[ASAI] Um. Who's that?

00:03:57.320 --> 00:03:58.571 position:50% align:center
You mean Uzaki?

00:03:58.655 --> 00:04:01.116 position:50% align:center
Oh, she goes to school with us.
She's a sophomore.

00:04:01.199 --> 00:04:03.410 position:50% align:center
Ah. She's in college?

00:04:03.493 --> 00:04:06.496 position:50% align:center
Almost forgot! I brought
that game you lent me.

00:04:06.579 --> 00:04:08.331 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Cool. Did ya like?

00:04:08.415 --> 00:04:12.210 position:50% align:center
[ASAI] They must be close if
they borrow each other's stuff.

00:04:12.293 --> 00:04:15.171 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI] I'll admit, that final
act was a real shocker!

00:04:15.255 --> 00:04:17.382 position:50% align:center
Here I thought it was an
entirely different game,

00:04:17.465 --> 00:04:19.926 position:50% align:center
but when I found out it was kind
of a sequel to the last one,

00:04:20.010 --> 00:04:21.469 position:50% align:center
it was like goosebump city!

00:04:21.553 --> 00:04:23.596 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah. For sure, right?

00:04:23.680 --> 00:04:25.724 position:50% align:center
I mean, I would've been happy
playing just a plain old

00:04:25.807 --> 00:04:28.476 position:50% align:center
building game, but it turned out
to be such a crazy-good find,

00:04:28.560 --> 00:04:30.812 position:50% align:center
I just had to get it out there,
you know what I mean?

00:04:30.895 --> 00:04:32.147 position:50% align:center
What's this?

00:04:32.230 --> 00:04:34.482 position:50% align:center
Since when is he such
good friends with a girl?

00:04:34.566 --> 00:04:37.152 position:50% align:center
[ASAI]
No! They can't be!

00:04:37.235 --> 00:04:38.153 position:50% align:center
[CAFÉ OWNER]
Oh, those two?

00:04:38.236 --> 00:04:40.363 position:50% align:center
[CAFÉ OWNER chuckles]

00:04:40.447 --> 00:04:43.074 position:50% align:center
[ASAI]
Dad. What's with the chuckle?

00:04:43.158 --> 00:04:45.201 position:50% align:center
[CAFÉ OWNER]
It's nothing, pumpkin.

00:04:45.285 --> 00:04:48.038 position:50% align:center
Bring her some water, would you?

00:04:48.121 --> 00:04:49.456 position:50% align:center
[ASAI]
Here you are.

00:04:49.539 --> 00:04:50.999 position:50% align:center
I appreciate it!

00:04:51.082 --> 00:04:53.001 position:50% align:center
I guess we go to
the same school.

00:04:53.084 --> 00:04:55.337 position:50% align:center
My name is Ami Asai.
I'm a senior.

00:04:55.420 --> 00:04:56.713 position:50% align:center
It's good to meet you!

00:04:56.796 --> 00:04:59.132 position:50% align:center
How cool that you're
the senior here!

00:04:59.215 --> 00:05:02.010 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] Be right back.
I'm gonna go put this in my bag.

00:05:02.093 --> 00:05:03.178 position:50% align:center
[CAFÉ OWNER]
Hm.

00:05:03.261 --> 00:05:05.764 position:50% align:center
Hana Uzaki.
I'm a sophomore!

00:05:05.847 --> 00:05:07.349 position:50% align:center
[giggles]

00:05:07.432 --> 00:05:11.436 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Now that I get a good
look at her, she's really cute!

00:05:11.519 --> 00:05:13.772 position:50% align:center
Look at her and that
endearing smile.

00:05:13.855 --> 00:05:14.981 position:50% align:center
And she's short,
so she's got this

00:05:15.065 --> 00:05:17.650 position:50% align:center
"adorable baby animal" vibe.

00:05:17.734 --> 00:05:22.447 position:50% align:center
But she's definitely not a baby.
I mean, wowzer! What the...?

00:05:22.530 --> 00:05:24.324 position:50% align:center
This girl's a beast!

00:05:24.407 --> 00:05:27.452 position:50% align:center
Okay, c'mon. Get it together!

00:05:27.535 --> 00:05:31.164 position:50% align:center
Ahem. You and Sakurai seem
like you get along great!

00:05:31.247 --> 00:05:33.291 position:50% align:center
Oh! Yeah, I guess we do!

00:05:33.375 --> 00:05:35.335 position:50% align:center
How long have you
known each other?

00:05:35.418 --> 00:05:38.505 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI] We were in the
same club in high school.

00:05:38.588 --> 00:05:40.965 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] The water on
Uzaki's table's getting low.

00:05:41.049 --> 00:05:42.842 position:50% align:center
Guess I should get it.

00:05:42.926 --> 00:05:44.678 position:50% align:center
He's always been
a big gloomy-face

00:05:44.761 --> 00:05:46.680 position:50% align:center
with an evil twinkle in his eye.

00:05:46.763 --> 00:05:49.015 position:50% align:center
He was a hard person
to get to know.

00:05:49.099 --> 00:05:51.810 position:50% align:center
Even now, in college,
he's gotten no better.

00:05:51.893 --> 00:05:54.020 position:50% align:center
I mean, he still skulks
around like a loner.

00:05:54.104 --> 00:05:56.356 position:50% align:center
So, I do my best
to look out for him!

00:05:56.439 --> 00:05:58.692 position:50% align:center
[ASAI]
Ah! So, that's how it is.

00:05:58.775 --> 00:06:00.235 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:06:00.318 --> 00:06:02.862 position:50% align:center
Well, just call me over whenever
you're ready to order, Hana.

00:06:02.946 --> 00:06:04.155 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
'Kay!

00:06:05.740 --> 00:06:07.742 position:50% align:center
What do you think?

00:06:07.826 --> 00:06:09.452 position:50% align:center
She's just so good!

00:06:09.536 --> 00:06:12.288 position:50% align:center
I know you want to stick
your nose in their business,

00:06:12.372 --> 00:06:15.291 position:50% align:center
but I feel like we really
shouldn't interfere, y'know?

00:06:15.375 --> 00:06:18.545 position:50% align:center
 It's just hard not to want
to guide them along a bit.

00:06:18.628 --> 00:06:20.130 position:50% align:center
I agree.

00:06:20.213 --> 00:06:22.632 position:50% align:center
Don't you love the
service industry?

00:06:22.716 --> 00:06:25.010 position:50% align:center
You get to be a fly on
the wall and watch people

00:06:25.093 --> 00:06:27.220 position:50% align:center
live their lives--
like those two.

00:06:27.303 --> 00:06:30.557 position:50% align:center
It's one of the thrills
of this business.

00:06:30.640 --> 00:06:32.142 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Oh. Uh?

00:06:32.225 --> 00:06:33.768 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Here's your water, Uzaki--

00:06:35.103 --> 00:06:38.398 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI groans]
Man, that's cold!

00:06:38.481 --> 00:06:41.067 position:50% align:center
Ugh! Sakurai, where the
heck did you come from?

00:06:41.151 --> 00:06:42.861 position:50% align:center
That's my line, you ass!

00:06:42.944 --> 00:06:44.946 position:50% align:center
Customers are supposed
to sit there, patiently.

00:06:45.030 --> 00:06:46.865 position:50% align:center
I was bringing the
water to the table!

00:06:46.948 --> 00:06:48.408 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Oh, don't gimme that crap!

00:06:48.491 --> 00:06:50.869 position:50% align:center
You haven't been treating me
like a real customer, anyway!

00:06:50.952 --> 00:06:52.412 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Just shut up!

00:06:52.495 --> 00:06:55.331 position:50% align:center
[CAFÉ OWNER] Wow, they put on
quite a show, don't they?

00:06:55.415 --> 00:06:56.833 position:50% align:center
[ASAI]
You're telling me.

00:06:56.916 --> 00:07:00.086 position:50% align:center
I've got to start
taking more shifts!

00:07:00.170 --> 00:07:03.131 position:50% align:center
[CAFÉ OWNER]
Oh, maybe give them a towel.

00:07:03.214 --> 00:07:05.508 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI sneezes]

00:07:07.093 --> 00:07:08.094 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
What?!

00:07:08.178 --> 00:07:09.637 position:50% align:center
So, he didn't come
in to work at all

00:07:09.721 --> 00:07:11.139 position:50% align:center
'cause he's down with a cold?

00:07:11.222 --> 00:07:14.100 position:50% align:center
Yep, Sakurai gave me a call
first thing this morning.

00:07:14.184 --> 00:07:15.602 position:50% align:center
Told him to take the day off.

00:07:15.685 --> 00:07:17.937 position:50% align:center
Prob'ly the result of the
ice-water drenching, yesterday,

00:07:18.021 --> 00:07:20.357 position:50% align:center
and the fact that it
got so cold last night.

00:07:20.440 --> 00:07:21.775 position:50% align:center
How 'bout that.

00:07:21.858 --> 00:07:23.026 position:50% align:center
So much for the whole,

00:07:23.109 --> 00:07:25.737 position:50% align:center
"Oh, yeah, I work out,"
tough-guy thing he does.

00:07:25.820 --> 00:07:28.698 position:50% align:center
Surprisingly fragile, that one.

00:07:28.782 --> 00:07:32.452 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Oh, yeah, I train.

00:07:32.535 --> 00:07:33.620 position:50% align:center
[ASAI, CAFE OWNER]
I don't get it.

00:07:33.703 --> 00:07:37.123 position:50% align:center
Why doesn't she
have a cold, then?

00:07:37.207 --> 00:07:39.626 position:50% align:center
In that case, sir,
check, please!

00:07:40.669 --> 00:07:45.632 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] Man, I have
been knocked flat.

00:07:45.715 --> 00:07:48.134 position:50% align:center
Did colds always hit this hard?

00:07:48.218 --> 00:07:51.221 position:50% align:center
I mean, do I need medicine?

00:07:51.304 --> 00:07:54.349 position:50% align:center
Oh, I guess I should try
to eat something first.

00:07:54.432 --> 00:07:57.268 position:50% align:center
--[grunts] I can't seem to move.
--[doorbell rings]

00:07:57.352 --> 00:07:58.978 position:50% align:center
Ugh, what now?

00:07:59.062 --> 00:08:02.649 position:50% align:center
[ringing continues]

00:08:02.732 --> 00:08:06.319 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] Damn, what a racket.
Who the heck is here?

00:08:06.403 --> 00:08:08.571 position:50% align:center
They're lucky I've even managed
to get myself outta bed.

00:08:08.655 --> 00:08:11.866 position:50% align:center
Hey, sicko! A little bird
told me you have a cold!

00:08:11.950 --> 00:08:13.535 position:50% align:center
I'm here to pay you a visit!

00:08:13.618 --> 00:08:15.704 position:50% align:center
Oh. Uzaki.

00:08:15.787 --> 00:08:18.331 position:50% align:center
What? How do you
know where I live?

00:08:18.415 --> 00:08:19.541 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:08:19.624 --> 00:08:21.459 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
U-Uh...

00:08:22.627 --> 00:08:25.797 position:50% align:center
Oh, no. Hey, you okay, there?

00:08:25.880 --> 00:08:28.216 position:50% align:center
A-Are you asleep?

00:08:33.680 --> 00:08:36.474 position:50% align:center
Wowee. That's a bad cold.

00:08:36.558 --> 00:08:38.435 position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:08:38.518 --> 00:08:40.812 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] Well, looks like
I've let her into my place,

00:08:40.895 --> 00:08:41.938 position:50% align:center
after all.

00:08:42.022 --> 00:08:42.772 position:50% align:center
Who was it?

00:08:42.856 --> 00:08:45.400 position:50% align:center
Who told you where I live?

00:08:45.483 --> 00:08:48.528 position:50% align:center
Oh. Was that wrong?

00:08:48.611 --> 00:08:51.865 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI sighs] Since I finally
found out where he lived,

00:08:51.948 --> 00:08:55.076 position:50% align:center
I thought maybe we could
do some gaming or whatever.

00:08:55.160 --> 00:08:57.620 position:50% align:center
Dude, talk about a let-down.

00:08:57.704 --> 00:09:00.123 position:50% align:center
This thing has really
wiped him out.

00:09:00.206 --> 00:09:02.959 position:50% align:center
He brags about stamina,
but a cold kicks his butt.

00:09:03.043 --> 00:09:04.669 position:50% align:center
Mm! Figures.

00:09:08.048 --> 00:09:09.716 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
That does it.

00:09:09.799 --> 00:09:12.552 position:50% align:center
Sakurai, have you seen a doctor?

00:09:12.635 --> 00:09:14.804 position:50% align:center
No. I can't move.

00:09:14.888 --> 00:09:16.056 position:50% align:center
Any meds?

00:09:16.139 --> 00:09:18.892 position:50% align:center
No. Haven't been
able to buy any.

00:09:18.975 --> 00:09:22.145 position:50% align:center
Then you haven't eaten, either.

00:09:22.228 --> 00:09:25.857 position:50% align:center
Well, all right, then.
Don't worry. Leave this to me!

00:09:28.777 --> 00:09:30.695 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Uh...

00:09:32.072 --> 00:09:33.865 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Oof.

00:09:36.076 --> 00:09:38.953 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI] This one's probably
best for his symptoms.

00:09:41.414 --> 00:09:43.792 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
A cold calls for leeks!

00:09:43.875 --> 00:09:48.880 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI pants]

00:09:51.675 --> 00:09:53.885 position:50% align:center
[groans]

00:09:56.054 --> 00:09:57.931 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Hey, can you sit up?

00:10:01.226 --> 00:10:04.979 position:50% align:center
Good, then try to eat.
Even if it's just a few bites.

00:10:08.024 --> 00:10:09.192 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI gasps]

00:10:09.275 --> 00:10:11.111 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI] It was a real adventure,
let me tell you!

00:10:11.194 --> 00:10:14.656 position:50% align:center
Empty fridge, awkward kitchen,
dirty cookers.

00:10:14.739 --> 00:10:17.367 position:50% align:center
So, now... open up!

00:10:17.450 --> 00:10:20.328 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
I, uh. I can feed myself.

00:10:21.871 --> 00:10:23.123 position:50% align:center
Would you stop?

00:10:23.206 --> 00:10:24.416 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI gasps]

00:10:33.133 --> 00:10:34.134 position:50% align:center
It's good.

00:10:34.217 --> 00:10:35.719 position:50% align:center
I know, right?

00:10:35.802 --> 00:10:40.181 position:50% align:center
Well, honestly, I'm not tasting
things very well right now.

00:10:40.265 --> 00:10:41.808 position:50% align:center
But it's probably good.

00:10:41.891 --> 00:10:44.978 position:50% align:center
"Probably," huh?
That's just great.

00:10:45.061 --> 00:10:46.396 position:50% align:center
Sorry.

00:10:56.281 --> 00:10:59.534 position:50% align:center
See? My cooking
is totally edible.

00:11:01.077 --> 00:11:02.328 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Thanks.

00:11:04.664 --> 00:11:06.750 position:50% align:center
Wow, eating really
warmed me up.

00:11:06.833 --> 00:11:09.627 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI] You got a good
sweat going on! Excellent!

00:11:09.711 --> 00:11:11.171 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Huh?

00:11:11.254 --> 00:11:13.423 position:50% align:center
Now, strip!

00:11:13.506 --> 00:11:14.924 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
No way.

00:11:15.008 --> 00:11:16.426 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Oh, yes way!

00:11:16.509 --> 00:11:18.261 position:50% align:center
